indelible.Blob - Hackathon Submission

Track: Provably Authentic (Truth Engine + Trust Oracle)
Team: Solo 
Submission Date: November 23, 2025




Project Overview

indelible.Blob is a decentralized imagery capture and verification platform that creates tamper-proof, blockchain-verified media with GPS provenance. By combining high-accuracy GPS tracking, Walrus decentralized storage, and Sui blockchain verification, indelible.Blob establishes an immutable chain of custody for digital evidence from the moment of capture.

Truth begins at the source. Verify everything.




The Problem: Crisis of Trust in Digital Media

In an era of deepfakes, AI-generated content, and widespread misinformation, trust in digital media has collapsed. News organizations, legal systems, insurance companies, and the public face an unprecedented challenge: How do you know what's real?

Current Pain Points

1.
Media Authenticity Crisis

•
Deepfakes are indistinguishable from reality

•
AI can generate convincing fake images and videos

•
Photo/video manipulation is trivial and undetectable

•
No reliable way to verify source or provenance

1.
Centralized Verification Failures

•
Traditional platforms can be compromised

•
Metadata can be stripped or falsified

•
Central authorities are single points of failure

•
No transparent chain of custody

1.
Legal & Insurance Challenges

•
Evidence authenticity is increasingly disputed

•
Insurance fraud detection is reactive, not proactive

•
Chain of custody documentation is manual and error-prone

•
No standardized verification framework

1.
Creator Rights & Attribution

•
Original creators lose control of their work

•
No provable ownership or licensing mechanism

•
Media organizations can't verify source reliability

•
Licensing terms are unenforceable




