•
Automated licensing and payments

•
Chain of custody documentation

•
Legal protection through provenance

1.
Economic Model

•
Creators earn from verified content

•
Media orgs pay for authenticity guarantee

•
Platform facilitates trust, not control

•
Decentralized governance

The Network Effect: Trust by Default

The Goal: Make indelible.Blob the de facto global standard for media verification.

The Strategy: Create a trust asymmetry where:

•
Verified content = Trusted by default

•
Unverified content = Inherently suspect

As more creators, news organizations, and institutions adopt indelible.Blob, unverified media becomes unusable because the uncertainty is built into its foundation. The platform doesn't need to prove unverified content is fake—the absence of verification becomes the red flag.

This creates a positive feedback loop:

1.
More verified content → Higher trust in platform

2.
Higher trust → More adoption by media orgs

3.
More adoption → More creator incentive

4.
More creators → Unverified content loses value

5.
Lost value → Pressure to verify → More adoption




