Technical Differentiation

Why Walrus?

Decentralized storage is non-negotiable for trust infrastructure.

•
Censorship resistance: No authority can remove verified evidence

•
Permanent availability: Content persists regardless of platform changes

•
Cryptographic verification: Blob IDs provide tamper-proof references

•
Cost efficiency: Decentralized storage scales better than centralized

Why Sui?

High-performance blockchain for real-time verification.

•
Fast finality: Verification happens in seconds, not minutes

•
Low cost: Affordable to verify every capture

•
Object model: Natural fit for media provenance tracking

•
Ecosystem: Growing developer community and institutional support

Why Seal + Nautilus?

Complete the decentralized truth infrastructure.

•
Seal: Privacy without sacrificing verification

•
Nautilus: Decentralized AI without centralized authority

•
Together: Full-stack solution for authenticated, private, intelligent media




Competitive Landscape

Existing Solutions

1.
Content Credentials (Adobe, C2PA)

•
Limitation: Centralized, metadata can be stripped, no blockchain verification

•
indelible.Blob advantage: Decentralized, immutable, cryptographically verifiable

1.
Blockchain Media Platforms (Arweave, IPFS)

•
Limitation: Storage only, no capture-time verification, no GPS provenance

•
indelible.Blob advantage: End-to-end verification from capture to storage

1.
Forensic Analysis Tools

•
Limitation: Reactive (detect tampering after the fact), expensive, not scalable

•
indelible.Blob advantage: Proactive (verify at capture), automatic, scales infinitely

1.
Traditional Media Verification

•
Limitation: Manual, slow, expensive, not transparent

•
indelible.Blob advantage: Automated, instant, transparent, decentralized

